The '''Lufira masked weaver''' ('''''Ploceus ruweti'''''), also known as '''Ruwet's masked weaver''' or the '''Lake Lufira weaver''', is a species of [[bird]] in the [[Ploceidae|weaver]] family, Ploceidae. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to the Democratic Republic of the Congo. Its natural [[habitat]] is [[swamp]]s in the south-east part of the country. It is sometimes regarded as a [[subspecies]] of the [[Tanzanian masked weaver]].

